rt of the total loan payoff but generally isn't deductible by heirs either under current tax law (home equity interest typically isn't deductible unless used for home improvements). Some people make voluntary interest payments (if their loan allows) specifically to generate current deductions, but this defeats the purpose of eliminating monthly payments. Consult your tax advisor about interest deductibility specific to your situation."}}]};
